    "It serves as a useful metric for assessing the consistency and reliability of categorical classifications, providing insights into the quality of annotations or the performance of classifiers compared to human annotators.",
    "Page 53 of 72 80",
    "Cost-related metrics thoroughly evaluate classifier performance by explicitly incorporating the costs associated with different misclassifications.",
    "These metrics go beyond traditional metrics and take into account the real-world impact of classification errors.",
    "By considering the consequences of misclassification, cost-related metrics offer a more nuanced and practical assessment of a classifier's effectiveness, especially in domains where misclassification costs are high, such as medicine."
